.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "May 2026" "Holberton School" "Simple Shell Man Page"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
[\fIfilename\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter (shell) written in C.
It reads commands from standard input in interactive or non-interactive mode,
parses them, and executes them using the execve system call.
.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
The shell displays a prompt
.B ($)
and waits for the user to type a command, then executes it.
.PP
.RS
$ ./hsh
.br
($) /bin/ls
.br
hsh main.c shell.h
.br
($) exit
.RE
.SH NON-INTERACTIVE MODE
Commands can be piped into the shell:
.PP
.RS
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.RE
.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell with status 0.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns 0 on success, or an error code if a command is not found.
